            <a name='Turn'></a>
            <h2>Turn Ity</h2>
            <p>Turn Ity is a Seattle area hula hooper who has been hooping for the past 5 years.  She started hooping for fitness through the Hoopgirl series, and has since found a love for hoopdance and fire spinning performance.  She is currently a performer/instructor with Seattle Fire Gate, Flamebouyant Productions*, and makes handcrafted hoops and fleather earrings for Turn Ity Creations.
            <ul>
               <li>Beginner Hooping:  Learn tips and tricks to keeping the hoop on your waist.  Explore the space in and around the hoop as a foundation for hoopdance.  <p>Participants should dress in comfortable/non-slippery/non-bulky clothing.</li>
               <li>Beginner/Intermediate: prerequisite (waist hooping) Get your heart rate pumping through combining basic hoopdance moves with strength building exercise.  Use the hoop as a tool to strengthen core muscles and increase endurance.</li>
            </ul>

            <a name='Kat'></a>
            <h2>Kat Tutty</h2>
            <p>Kat Tutty is a Hoop Dancer based our of Victoria who remains committed to flow as a practice that unifies the self with community.  After gaining discovering so much emotional well being through her hoop practice, she committed herself to furthering that well being in the community.<p>She has founded and continues to lead a Hoop Club through UVic which proudly holds 110 current registered members.<p>https://www.facebook.com/pages/Uvics-Hoop-Love-Club/415695735145809<p>She is leading the "Let the People Flow" project - a broad contemporary flow arts platform that is set for release in the coming months.
            <ul>
               <li>Connecting the Dots: Beginner - this class connects  your flow practice first to the body and then to your prop.  Through music, movement and dance, this workshop will lead you through exercises that will express flow as a scale of connected movements.  The focus will be on ecstatic dance, and restoring and maintaining the flow body.</li>
               <li>Discover unity through a hoop -- This is a partner workshop designed to inspire intimacy with the self, their space and the members of the community.  This workshop will invite participants to hold space with themselves, and others, through partner work exercises, and honest reflections.</li>
                
            </ul>

            <a name='Laurel'></a>
            <h2>Laurel Collins</h2>
            <p>Laurel found her passion for dance inside the hoop and has been a hoop addict ever since. After learning from and teaching with Pixie Hoops, she left the west coast to spend some time touring across Canada and back giving workshops, hoop performances and fire shows. While she's flirted with fire fans, poi and double staff, the hoop is still her one true love. Now back in Victoria, her latest flow projects have focused on partner hooping and deepening her connection to play inside and outside the hoop.<p>Hoop Performance:<p>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kgv9kQ_T_BE<p>Partner Hooping<p>http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DHx0iXmRfQ0&amp;feature=share&amp;list=UUYgU_gkVlinYVXOa1QyJBgA<p>Http://compassionvictoria.wix.com/hoopflow
            <ul>
               <li>Partner Hoop: This workshop will give you two-person hoop skills for performance duos or partner play. Learn 'partner-transfers', the 'face-to-face partner weave', 'angel's embrace', 'around the clock' and much more. <p>Intermediate (It would be best if participants were already comfortable with the basic hooping around the waist, the 'one-hoop forward weave' and horizontal hand hooping above the head)</li>
               <li>Hoop Play Find a new connection with your hoop, or deepen an old one. This workshop is designed to expand our range of play, destabilize our current frameworks, open new pathways and release us into new possibilities.<p>All levels</li>
            </ul>

            <a name='Christa'></a>
            <h2>Christa Giles</h2>
            <p>Christa has taught monthly workshops and weekly Hoop Play classes in Vancouver since 2006, and helps organize Vancouver's Madskillz Festival each June. Learn more at http://christahoops.com.
            <ul>
               <li>Air Time for Hoopers! Throw your hoop up in the air! Learn a variety of tosses, throws, flips, and spins to add some off-body flair to your play sessions or performances. All levels welcome, please bring your own hoop. Christa will have a few loaners available: first come, first served.</li>
               <li>Advanced Hoop Weaves: Two-hoop toss combos, twisting weaves and more - this workshop broke brains at last year's Madskillz Festival! Hoopers should be comfortable with forward and reverse three-beat-weave, please bring your own hoops. Christa will have a few loaner sets available: first come, first served.</li>
