            <a name='Blake'></a>
            <h2>Blake Speers </h2>
            <p>Blake Speers is mostly a government worker but occasionally tosses things around randomly for his own amusement. He is a Juggler with more than 10 years experience goofing around with things that fall down. He has run school juggling programs for almost half that time in Canada and the UK and taught juggling theory at the IJA, EJC and Online. 
            <ul>
               <li>Wrist Traps and Variations for Clubs/Sticks- An expansive workshop on wrist traps for anything that's long and has a narrow part. Emphasis will be placed on crossover skills between different kinds of props, and other stuff.</li>
