            <ul>
            <li>Pass it to me!: Most jugglers know how to teach beginners to juggler three balls and there is a standard approach (start with one ball, practice with both hands, etc). However, there is no such standard approach for teaching passing. This workshop demonstrates a method for teaching ambidextrous jugglers and not-yet-jugglers to pass with a very specific set of steps.<p>All skill levels welcome as it helps to have both people that want to learn to pass as well as people that want to learn to teach others to pass. Bring clubs.<p>This curriculum is outlined here: http://passingpedagogy.com (a work in progress).</li>
               <li>Pass me by: 3 (or 4) beginning side-by-side passing patterns for intermediate passers. These patterns are siteswap based (don't worry, it's simple siteswap, just 3s and 2s), and visually interesting.</li>
